Commentary Text: Fazalhaq Farooqi to Hetmyer, 2 runs, comedy of errors! Comical scenes everywhere. A very full delivery outside off, carved to Mayank at sweeper cover, Ashwin does not want the 2nd, but Hetmyer does, they almost run into each other, but avoid, there is a clear run-out chance at Fazalhaq Farooqi's end, but the bowler fumbles the throw to draw a puzzled reaction from Mayank. Ashwin was well out had Farooqi collected and broken the stumps. Amidst all this, they check for a short run too, but Hetmyer has plonked his bat over the line. Phew!

Commentary Text: Umran Malik to Padikkal, out Bowled!! Commentary Text: Chahal to Harry Brook, out Bowled!! Chahal strikes and that ends a scratchy first innings for Harry Brook in the IPL! 300 wickets for Chahal in T20s, informs the on air commentator. He bowls it quicker and flatter on off, perhaps the flipper. Harry Brook expects it to spin away as he rocks back in an attempt to cut it square of the wicket on the off-side. Is done in by the skidiness on the ball and the ball crashes into the off-stump. SRH are in a lot of trouble now. Harry Brook b Chahal 13(21) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Boult to Tripathi, out Caught by Holder!! What a catch! Tripathi is going nowhere. He thinks it is a bump-ball. Surprisingly Tripathi reviews and umpire KN Anantha Padmanabhan is having a word with the batter. Is this an umpire's review or a batter's review? It is the batter's. Outstanding catch by the tall Holder, stretching his left-hand and grabbing it at a wide slip. Tripathi came down the track and opened the face on this full outswinger outside off, guided it wide of Holder but the big man just plucked it from thin air. One of the moments of the IPL season already. SRH lose their review too. Tripathi c Holder b Boult 0(2)
